transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, John. I thought I submitted for a refill. I don't know, last week maybe or something like that.

Speaker 1: Can I get your zip code?

Speaker 2: Yeah, it's Gary Ryan, R-H-E-I-N, and the zip code is 45039.

Speaker 1: Thanks, Gary. One second, please.

Speaker 2: Okay, I see. Hackney Circle, right?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: So yeah, you put this order in on Sunday, and you didn't know this because I don't think it shows you on your site,

Speaker 1: but your prescription needed to be renewed, so we had to get that renewed.

Speaker 2: It just got approved today, so they'll ship it out probably tomorrow.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay. Well, I mean, there's no hurry. I just hadn't received any information.

Speaker 2: I was, you know, not sure what was going on.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's what happened, so that's why you haven't heard anything,

Speaker 2: but you should get an email probably tomorrow with tracking.

Speaker 1: Okay, great. Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: Thanks, sir. Have a good one.

Speaker 1: You too. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
